Hmm.  Guess there really is no way to disagree with that old sport.  The US has certainly shown the world what happens if a tiger gets its tail pulled. (Probably a poor metaphor, but you know what I mean.)<br>
<br>
The might and determination to get things done of the US has never been in any doubt (since a long time.)  When you're powerful it's easy to forget to also be wise and merciful.<br>
<br>
The voice of the dissident is here to remind everyone of that awful responsibility.  In a sense it's democracy at work right?<br>
The whole concept of debate, a ruling party v. the 'opposition', <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>all</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> possible arguments given an airing if only to see if they stand up.<br>
<br>
